T1  - Strategic Interventions in Intellectual Asset Flows
AU  - Mcgaughey, Sara L.
Y1  - 2002/04/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2002.6588008
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2002.6588008
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 248
EP  - 274
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The rise of the knowledge economy brings to the foreground questions of how firms might best capture the value of their intellectual assets. In this article I introduce the notion of strategic interventions in intellectual asset flows designed to influence the level and composition of intellectual asset scarcity, with implications for firm performance. I also present propositions that explain and predict how contingencies at differing levels of analysis influence the choice of strategic intervention.
AB  - The rise of the knowledge economy brings to the foreground questions of how firms might best capture the value of their intellectual assets. In this article I introduce the notion of strategic interventions in intellectual asset flows designed to influence the level and composition of intellectual asset scarcity, with implications for firm performance. I also present propositions that explain and predict how contingencies at differing levels of analysis influence the choice of strategic intervention.
