N2  - Commentary is presented for the article ?Taking time to integrate temporal research,? by D. G. Ancona, G. A. Okhuysen and L.A. Perlow, published in a 2001 issue of ?Academy of Management Review.? According to the author, the article divides time as it pertains to temporal research into five categories, event time?predictable, event time?unpredictable clock time, cyclical time, and life cycle. The author looks to replace the article's dealing of cyclical time with the concept of ?makimono time.?
AB  - Commentary is presented for the article ?Taking time to integrate temporal research,? by D. G. Ancona, G. A. Okhuysen and L.A. Perlow, published in a 2001 issue of ?Academy of Management Review.? According to the author, the article divides time as it pertains to temporal research into five categories, event time?predictable, event time?unpredictable clock time, cyclical time, and life cycle. The author looks to replace the article's dealing of cyclical time with the concept of ?makimono time.?
