TY  - JOUR
T1  - Institutional Contradictions, Praxis, and Institutional Change: A Dialectical Perspective
AU  - Seo, Myeong-Gu
AU  - Creed, W. E. Douglas
Y1  - 2002/04/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2002.6588004
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2002.6588004
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 222
EP  - 247
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We use a dialectical perspective to provide a unique framework for understanding institutional change that more fully captures its totalistic, historical, and dynamic nature, as well as fundamentally resolves a theoretical dilemma of institutional theory: the relative swing between agency and embeddedness. In this framework institutional change is understood as an outcome of the dynamic interactions between two institutional by-products: institutional contradictions and human praxis. In particular, we depict praxis?agency embedded in a totality of multiple levels of interpenetrating, incompatible institutional arrangements (contradictions)?as an essential driving force of institutional change.
AB  - We use a dialectical perspective to provide a unique framework for understanding institutional change that more fully captures its totalistic, historical, and dynamic nature, as well as fundamentally resolves a theoretical dilemma of institutional theory: the relative swing between agency and embeddedness. In this framework institutional change is understood as an outcome of the dynamic interactions between two institutional by-products: institutional contradictions and human praxis. In particular, we depict praxis?agency embedded in a totality of multiple levels of interpenetrating, incompatible institutional arrangements (contradictions)?as an essential driving force of institutional change.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2002.6588004
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2002.6588004
Y2  - 2026/04/24
